targets.docString: Support different 'any' behaviours for different targets. All targets are optional and will be tried from most specific to least specific.

validatorExpression.docString: Expression that synchronously resolves to a boolean. Should be 'true' if the input is valid, and 'false' otherwise. Interpolates '$value$' with the current property that is being validated

validatorImport.docString: A raw import that is added to the files where the provided validator expression is used.

structure.docString: Enable a structure dump. This way this structure can be reused via 'Generator#addStructure

openApiRouteExtensions.docString: Add or overwrite specific properties per route. The keys should be formatted as 'upperCaseFirst(group) + upperCaseFirst(name)'.

router.docString: Generate a validating router with entry points for your route handlers.

target.docString: Select one of the supported libraries to generate a router for.

exposeApiStructure.docString: Adds a Compas '_compas/structure.json' route to the generated router that includes all available routes.

database.docString: Generate one of the compatible database interfaces.

target.docString: Select one of the supported dialects to generate queries for.

includeDDL.docString: Write out 'common/structure.sql' with a naive DDL approach.

includeEntityDiagram.docString: Create a markdown file containing the ERD in a 'mermaid' block.

validators.docString: Alter the output of generated validators. Other generators will always include validators in their output if necessary.

includeBaseTypes.docString: Always generate validators for all named types even if no other generator needs it. This implies {@link ExperimentalGenerateOptions.generators.types.includeBaseTypes}.

apiClient.docString: Generate an API client, based on the routes in your structure.

target.docString: Select your HTTP client of choice.

includeWrapper.docString: Include an API client wrapper to use the api easier with your user interface library.

globalClient.docString: Use a global api client that will be used for all requests. Only applicable when using 'axios'.

responseValidation.docString: Determine how strict the API client response validations are. This defaults to loose object validation, allowing extra values in the responses which are not returned in the validated result. It is advised to disable this when you use the API client for e2e testing your server.

types.docString: Alter the output of the generated types, they are always generated as a result of other enabled generators.

includeBaseTypes.docString: Always generate types for all named types even if no other generator needs it.

declareGlobalTypes.docString: Declare all types in the global namespace. Only applicable when using 'targetLanguage' when set to 'js' or 'ts'.

namedTypeDefinition.docString: This contains all types that can be added top level to the structure.
namedTypeDefinition.name: namedTypeDefinition

typeDefinition.docString: This contains all known type definitions.
typeDefinition.name: typeDefinition

typeSystemDefinition.docString: All type definitions that can be used inside other types, like object keys.
typeSystemDefinition.name: typeSystemDefinition
